d promoting children’s health and development. In a final chapter, the author appraises the major discoveries that have emerged during the three research generations and analyzes recent scientific agendas and discoveries in the peer relations discipline.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFriendship in children. 0aInterpersonal relations in children. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aKazdin, Alan E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010643540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014585440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300145854423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300145854/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY